════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Quiet and established with strong community appeal.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Tarragindi is a quiet, well-established suburb with wide streets, good schools and a strong family feel. Its central location and relative affordability compared to surrounding inner suburbs make it attractive to buyers seeking quality without the premium price tag.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I understand the buyer profile active in Tarragindi and the broader inner-south market. My campaigns are tailored to attract those buyers and build the kind of competition that produces exceptional results.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Toohey Forest borders Tarragindi to the east and south, providing one of the largest continuous bushland reserves close to Brisbane's inner city and giving the suburb a green, natural character that buyers from denser areas find genuinely attractive. The quiet internal streets are a deliberate contrast to the arterial roads that frame the suburb, and families who discover that pocket invariably become committed buyers. Community infrastructure including Tarragindi State School and local parks reflects the suburb's established, owner-occupier foundations. Demand from buyers who have been outpriced in Holland Park and Greenslopes has been steadily pushing Tarragindi values upward over recent sale cycles.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Tarragindi Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Inner South Brisbane</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Established Suburb</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Strong family community</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:#78716c;margin-top:2rem;">Also selling in: <a href="/suburbs/holland-park" style="color:#c4912a;">Holland Park</a>, <a href="/suburbs/mount-gravatt" style="color:#c4912a;">Mount Gravatt</a>, <a href="/suburbs/greenslopes" style="color:#c4912a;">Greenslopes</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

